TEXT.P:
Chung said Taiwan's environment is diverse and beautiful;
however, he lamented, the environment has been rapidly degraded due
to over-exploitation.

Liu by this time had run out of money and could not afford to pay
for flight tickets to return to Taiwan through Hong Kong or Macau,
which are the regular routes prescribed for ordinary travelers.

Exhibitors at the exposition represent more than 100 companies
from Taiwan, the United States, Canada, Australia, Germany, Austria,
South Africa and Thailand.

All of the eight major stock categories gained ground, with
foodstuff issues increasing the most at 4.9 percent; followed by
textiles at 1.7 percent; construction issues at 1.5 percent;
machinery and electronics shares at 1.4 percent; both financial and
cement stocks at 1.1 percent; paper and pulp issues at 0.9 percent;
and plastics at 0.3 percent.

Lee also outlined the DPP administration's major policy
achievements with regard to labor rights, including implementing a
shortened work-week system; workplace gender equality legislation;
implementation of an occupational accident labor protection law;
establishment of a new labor pension system; an increase in labor
insurance reimbursement; unemployment benefits; the offering of soft
loans for workers in need; improvement in foreign labor management;
reducing the number occupational accidents; job promotion; and
regulation of mass layoffs.
